               <p>JOHN FOWLE. I am an <rs id="t18301209-217-viclabel1213" type="occupation">oilman, and keep a shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-217-victim1855 t18301209-217-viclabel1213"></join> in <placeName id="t18301209-217-crimeloc1214">Anchor and Hope-alley, St. George's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-217-crimeloc1214" type="placeName" value="Anchor and Hope-alley, St. George's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-217-crimeloc1214" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-217-off1211 t18301209-217-crimeloc1214"></join>. On the 15th of November I was in my back premises, and saw the prisoner come into my shop, and lean over the counter; he put something into his trousers pocket - he leaned over a second time, and while he was doing so I ran up; he got out, but I caught him just outside the shop; I asked what he had taken from the till - he said he had not touched it; I took him round, and did not miss any thing from the till; I asked what he had in his pocket - he said it was nothing to me; I then recollected that I had counted 5s. worth of penny-pieces, and put them behind my counter - I went to them, and found only 2s. 2d. left; on the prisoner I found 2s. 10d., which made up the 5s. - the prisoner said he sold ducks about the street; the officer took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-217-person1856">
                  CHARLES 
                  FALCONER
               <interp inst="t18301209-217-person1856" type="surname" value="FALCONER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-217-person1856" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-217-person1856" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the officer. I took him, and have the money.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He took me into the shop, said he had been robbed before, and he would make me suffer for all.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18301209-217-verdict1215" type="verdictDescription">
